t: 26px;"><div class=3D"body markup" dir=3D"auto" style=3D"text-align: init=
ial;font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;width: 100%;word-break: break-word;ma=
rgin-bottom: 16px;font-family: Lora,sans-serif;font-weight: 400;"><p style=
=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16=
px;margin-top: 0;"><span>Substack on Film originated from a very analog exp=
erience: watching my friend </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect=
/7b1b5a48-e48a-4802-90b6-619322148f21?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMW5qZ29rIn0.AgI-vvm-koCou=
pjCwZXCGwdYu_D1iw9ecHmePkbA3ys" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: #ff7731;text-decor=
ation: none;">Nate&#8217;s</a><span> work, filming 16mm advertisements for =
local businesses and screening them at local independent movie theaters. I =
approached him with an idea: What if we made these sorts of films, but for =
Substackers?</span></p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);=
line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"><span>We only planned to make one seaso=
n&#8212;just five episodes, each featuring a different creator going about =
their daily life in and around San Francisco. Then we read the comments. Vi=
ewers called the episodes &#8220;</span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/red=
irect/e96661ed-e438-462f-9c50-3af20f38bfa9?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMW5qZ29rIn0.AgI-vvm-=
koCoupjCwZXCGwdYu_D1iw9ecHmePkbA3ys" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: #ff7731;text-=
decoration: none;">magnetic</a><span>,&#8221; &#8220;</span><a href=3D"http=
s://substack.com/redirect/3b2a25d8-38cc-4ebe-8bd1-1429e8b798a1?j=3DeyJ1Ijoi=
MW5qZ29rIn0.AgI-vvm-koCoupjCwZXCGwdYu_D1iw9ecHmePkbA3ys" rel=3D"" style=3D"=
color: #ff7731;text-decoration: none;">thought-provoking</a><span>,&#8221; =
and &#8220;</span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/c37ea186-6a09-4e=
07-ac2e-dda97ee4ec7c?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMW5qZ29rIn0.AgI-vvm-koCoupjCwZXCGwdYu_D1iw=
9ecHmePkbA3ys" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: #ff7731;text-decoration: none;">ful=
l of wonderful reminders that the world isn&#8217;t as grim as they would h=
ave us believe</a><span>.&#8221; Our subscribers care about the creative li=
fe, and Substack on Film enables us to showcase the many ways it can look. =
So we decided to keep going.</span></p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color=
: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">The idea to do the next=
 season in London actually came from our co-founder Hamish. He&#8217;d just=
 returned from the city, still buzzing from the energy of the writers and c=
reators he&#8217;d met there. London is, of course, a historic city of lett=
ers, and home to our second-biggest share of bestsellers on the platform. A=
nd we&#8217;re an international bunch&#8212;just look at our co-founders. H=
amish is a Kiwi from New Zealand, Jairaj is Indian and grew up in Japan, an=
d Chris is Canadian. We&#8217;re headquartered in the USA, but Substack is =
global, baby.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-h=
eight: 26px;font-size: 16px;"><span>For the first episode of our London sea=
son, we met up with Laura Jackson, the </span><a href=3D"https://substack.c=
om/redirect/99f12935-c5f6-44e3-b309-f7b4ac41de9b?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMW5qZ29rIn0.Ag=
I-vvm-koCoupjCwZXCGwdYu_D1iw9ecHmePkbA3ys" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: #ff7731=
;text-decoration: none;">Glassette</a><span> co-founder, broadcaster, and m=
other of three. Thanks to a Tube strike, our local cinematographer, </span>=
<a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/37da3c5b-4649-4bc5-a546-d575063e97=
7b?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMW5qZ29rIn0.AgI-vvm-koCoupjCwZXCGwdYu_D1iw9ecHmePkbA3ys" rel=
=3D"" style=3D"color: #ff7731;text-decoration: none;">Daj</a><span>, our so=
und recordist, </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/98e51d96-d8a=
f-4ecb-b5a7-3e24089c3ea9?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMW5qZ29rIn0.AgI-vvm-koCoupjCwZXCGwdYu_=
D1iw9ecHmePkbA3ys" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: #ff7731;text-decoration: none;"=
>Nick</a><span>, and I took an incredibly long Uber ride from West London t=
o Hackney Depot, where we found Laura hard at work under the expansive skyl=
ight of a converted bus station.</span></p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;c=
olor: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">Laura has had a fas=
cinating career, finding her way through event management, broadcasting, an=
d, ultimately, starting her own e-commerce business. She&#8217;s also charm=
ing. A native of Northern England who dropped into East London nearly 20 ye=
ars ago, you can still hear the north in her accent. We watched Laura assem=
ble a moodboard and then take a coffee break, strolling Broadway Market, sh=
aking hands, kissing babies and dogs, and waving to friends real and imagin=
ary.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26=
px;font-size: 16px;margin-bottom: 0;">I hope you enjoy our first installmen=
t of Substack on Film: London. There&#8217;ll be more episodes in the comin=
g weeks. And let us know: Where should we film next?</p></div></div><div cl=
